# Iteration 1 Plan – MyClean App

## Dates
- **Start:** 3 March 2025  
- **End:**   24 March 2025

## Goal
Deliver a working MVP that supports the full booking flow:
Cleaner creates profile → Customer books → Cleaner receives notification → Customer pays.

## Task Assignment

| Task                                | Team Member          | Priority | Estimate |
|-------------------------------------|----------------------|----------|----------|
| Create and manage cleaner profile   | Asmita Sharma        | High     | 3 days   |
| Build customer booking interface    | Saung Hnin Phyu      | High     | 5 days   |
| Implement booking notifications     | Juninho Chandra      | Medium   | 2 days   |
| Develop mock online payment module  | Jiang Jinsong        | High     | 4 days   |
| Manage availability calendar        | Asmita Sharma        | High     | 3 days   |

## Week-by-Week Breakdown

| Week             | Objectives & Tasks                                                                                            | Checkpoint                                          |
|------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| **Week 1**<br>(3–9 Mar)   | • Create UI wireframes in Figma or NinjaMock<br>• Scaffold basic page layouts (Profile & Calendar)<br>• Draft database schema | Commit wireframe images and schema draft            |
| **Week 2**<br>(10–16 Mar) | • Implement profile form and booking page<br>• Add booking submission and notification logic<br>• Sketch mock payment page       | Demo booking flow screenshot                        |
| **Week 3**<br>(17–24 Mar) | • Integrate front-end and back-end prototypes<br>• Perform user acceptance tests<br>• Fix major bugs and record results          | Publish iteration 1 summary page with demo link     |

## Deliverables
1. UI wireframes and database ER diagram  
2. Profile, booking, notification, and payment prototypes  
3. User acceptance test report  
4. GitHub Pages documentation with screenshots and iteration log
